SIMPLE: unyoked
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unyoked
<hw>Un*yoked"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[In sense 1 pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>yoked</ets>; in senses 2 and 3 properly p. p.
of <ets>unyoke</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not yet yoked; not having worn the yoke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Freed or loosed from a yoke.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Licentious; unrestrained.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unyolden</ent>⟦br⟧
